Cottonwood Creek Instream Flow to Habitat Area Relationship

A dataset containing the Weighted Usable Area (WUA) in square feet per 1000 feet as a function of flow in cubic feet per second

cottonwood_creek_instream

Format

dataframe with 36 rows and 5 variables:

flow_cfs

integer flow value in cubic feet per second

FR_spawn_wua

spawning WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

FR_fry_wua

fry (up to 50 mm) WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

FR_juv_wua

juvenile WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

watershed

name of watershed

Source

CDFW 1979 and FWS 2014

Details

The spawning WUA values were derived from a PHABSIM model. The rearing values are from the FWS 2014 River2D model. The results are for Fall Run.
